statements: SELECT * FROM MachineLearningFeatures;
SELECT feature_id, feature_name FROM MachineLearningFeatures WHERE is_categorical = TRUE;
SELECT data_type FROM MachineLearningFeatures WHERE feature_id IN (1, 3, 5);
SELECT feature_name FROM MachineLearningFeatures WHERE data_type = 'Numeric' ORDER BY feature_name DESC;
SELECT feature_name, data_type FROM MachineLearningFeatures WHERE is_categorical = FALSE LIMIT 3;
SELECT * FROM MachineLearningFeatures WHERE data_type = 'numeric' ORDER BY feature_name DESC LIMIT 3
SELECT feature_id, feature_name FROM MachineLearningFeatures WHERE is_categorical = TRUE ORDER BY feature_id
SELECT feature_name, data_type FROM MachineLearningFeatures WHERE is_categorical = FALSE
SELECT * FROM MachineLearningFeatures WHERE data_type = 'text'
SELECT feature_id, feature_name, data_type, is_categorical FROM MachineLearningFeatures ORDER BY data_type
SELECT * FROM ml_features;
SELECT id, feature_name FROM ml_features ORDER BY feature_name DESC;
SELECT id, feature_name, data_type FROM ml_features WHERE data_type = 'numeric';
SELECT id, label_name, category FROM ml_labels WHERE category = 'target' ORDER BY id;
SELECT id, feature_name, description FROM ml_features;
SELECT * FROM ml_features WHERE id = 1;
SELECT description, feature_name FROM ml_features WHERE data_type = 'numeric';
SELECT label_name, category FROM ml_labels WHERE label_type = 'binary' ORDER BY label_name ASC;
SELECT * FROM ml_labels WHERE category = 'Finance' OR category = 'Healthcare';
SELECT feature_name, data_type, description FROM ml_features WHERE id IN (2, 4, 6);
SELECT * FROM features ORDER BY feature_name DESC
SELECT feature_id, feature_name FROM features WHERE feature_type = 'Temperature'
SELECT feature_id, feature_name, feature_type FROM features WHERE feature_value > 0
SELECT feature_name, feature_type, feature_value FROM features ORDER BY feature_value ASC
SELECT DISTINCT feature_type FROM features
SELECT * FROM features WHERE feature_type = 'numeric' ORDER BY feature_value DESC, feature_name ASC
SELECT feature_name, AVG(feature_value) FROM features GROUP BY feature_name HAVING AVG(feature_value) > 50
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT feature_type) AS num_feature_types FROM features
SELECT feature_type, COUNT(*) AS num_features FROM features GROUP BY feature_type ORDER BY num_features DESC
SELECT feature_name, feature_type, SUM(feature_value) AS total_value FROM features WHERE feature_value > 100 GROUP BY feature_name, feature_type ORDER BY total_value DESC
SELECT * FROM feature_extraction WHERE id = 1;
SELECT feature_name, feature_value FROM feature_extraction ORDER BY feature_value DESC;
SELECT id, dataset_id, normalization_method FROM data_preprocessing WHERE normalization_method = 'min-max';
SELECT model_name, algorithm_type FROM model_training WHERE algorithm_type = 'Random Forest';
SELECT model_id, evaluation_metric, evaluation_score FROM model_evaluation WHERE evaluation_score > 0.8 ORDER BY evaluation_score DESC;
SELECT * FROM feature_extraction ORDER BY id DESC;
SELECT feature_name, feature_value FROM feature_extraction WHERE feature_value > 0.5;
SELECT model_name, algorithm_type, accuracy_score FROM model_training WHERE accuracy_score >= 0.8 ORDER BY accuracy_score DESC;
SELECT model_id, evaluation_metric, evaluation_score FROM model_evaluation WHERE evaluation_score < 0.05 ORDER BY evaluation_score;
SELECT dataset_id, normalization_method FROM data_preprocessing ORDER BY dataset_id ASC;
SELECT * FROM features;
SELECT feature_name, feature_type FROM features ORDER BY feature_name DESC;
SELECT feature_id, feature_name, feature_value FROM features WHERE feature_type = 'numeric';
SELECT * FROM training_data WHERE label_id = 1 ORDER BY sample_id ASC;
SELECT feature_name, AVG(feature_value) AS avg_value FROM features GROUP BY feature_name;
SELECT feature_id, feature_name, feature_type FROM features;
SELECT feature_name, feature_value FROM features WHERE feature_type='numeric';
SELECT sample_id, sample_data FROM data_samples ORDER BY sample_id DESC;
SELECT label_name, COUNT(training_id) as num_samples FROM labels INNER JOIN training_data ON labels.label_id = training_data.label_id GROUP BY label_name;
SELECT parameter_name, MAX(parameter_value) as max_value FROM model_parameters;
